00:34:00.645 --> 00:34:03.020
SPEAKER 1: So I want to open
it up to audience questions.

00:34:03.020 --> 00:34:05.020
So we have two
microphones on each side.

00:34:05.020 --> 00:34:07.910
While people are lining up, Eva,
I've got a question for you.

00:34:07.910 --> 00:34:09.624
The last couple of
years, you've become

00:34:09.624 --> 00:34:10.790
a little bit of a celebrity.

00:34:10.790 --> 00:34:13.260
You were the Grand
Marshal of the Indy 500.

00:34:13.260 --> 00:34:15.830
You've become friends with
Ray Allen and Motley Crue

00:34:15.830 --> 00:34:17.362
and all kinds of people.

00:34:17.362 --> 00:34:19.070
Who's your favorite
celebrity that you've

00:34:19.070 --> 00:34:20.940
got to meet the last few years?

00:34:20.940 --> 00:34:25.850
EVA KOR: It's a very
incorrect question to ask me.

00:34:25.850 --> 00:34:28.730
I like all celebrities
and actually

00:34:28.730 --> 00:34:32.929
all people who are interested
in learning about the Holocaust,

00:34:32.929 --> 00:34:34.830
learning about forgiveness.

00:34:34.830 --> 00:34:39.350
It is each person
relates to it different.

00:34:39.350 --> 00:34:44.179
Ray Allen is a member of
the US Holocaust Council,

00:34:44.179 --> 00:34:46.400
and he has a special
interest in it.

00:34:46.400 --> 00:34:49.040
Then I met him, this tall guy.

00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:53.120
With all his family, he
came to Miami to my lecture.

00:34:53.120 --> 00:34:57.220
And he was interested
in what I had to say.

00:34:57.220 --> 00:34:59.120
I was very surprised
that he brought

00:34:59.120 --> 00:35:01.520
all of his five children.

00:35:01.520 --> 00:35:06.710
And with Motley Crew it
was strange, very strange.

00:35:06.710 --> 00:35:14.690
Nikki Sixx, his burley hair
appeared above my shoulder,

00:35:14.690 --> 00:35:18.140
as he was putting his
arm on my shoulder.

00:35:18.140 --> 00:35:22.100
And I saw this dangling
arm with all the tattoos.

00:35:22.100 --> 00:35:24.090
And I didn't even
know where on earth I

00:35:24.090 --> 00:35:27.980
was, because I just turned
around on the red carpet

00:35:27.980 --> 00:35:29.390
to find the right direction.

00:35:29.390 --> 00:35:30.140
You were there.

00:35:30.140 --> 00:35:31.250
TED GREEN: I was there.

00:35:31.250 --> 00:35:33.090
EVA KOR: And I'm
trying to figure out

00:35:33.090 --> 00:35:35.300
what on earth is happening.

00:35:35.300 --> 00:35:40.560
And he smiles with his big
mustache and lots of hair.

00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:42.450
"Hi, sweetie."

00:35:42.450 --> 00:35:45.020
I'm saying, well, I'm
on the red carpet.

00:35:45.020 --> 00:35:45.640
What do I do?

00:35:45.640 --> 00:35:46.350
I said hi.

00:35:49.400 --> 00:35:52.733
And then everybody told
me he was this famous.

00:35:52.733 --> 00:35:57.390
Well, I have texted to him
later on, a year later, I said,

00:35:57.390 --> 00:35:58.790
you scared me to death.

00:35:58.790 --> 00:36:00.830
Lucky that you had a nice smile.

00:36:00.830 --> 00:36:02.310
That put me at ease.

00:36:02.310 --> 00:36:04.970
I mean, I did not--

00:36:04.970 --> 00:36:09.380
I expected to meet media,
maybe in suits or at least

00:36:09.380 --> 00:36:10.580
more civilized looking.

00:36:13.697 --> 00:36:15.530
TED GREEN: You know,
what you're leaving out

00:36:15.530 --> 00:36:19.190
is right after the event, she
tweeted him and said, how do I

00:36:19.190 --> 00:36:21.260
get to be a rock star like you?

00:36:21.260 --> 00:36:22.874
And he responded--

00:36:22.874 --> 00:36:24.530
EVA KOR: "Well,
sweetie, you have

00:36:24.530 --> 00:36:27.200
been a rock star all your life.

00:36:27.200 --> 00:36:29.720
You have inspired many people."

00:36:29.720 --> 00:36:33.780
So then I appeared on his
radio show about a year ago.

00:36:33.780 --> 00:36:36.530
But it is-- here we are.

00:36:36.530 --> 00:36:38.330
I mean, lots of celebrities.

00:36:38.330 --> 00:36:42.410
I need all the celebrities,
I need all the everybody

00:36:42.410 --> 00:36:46.820
to join in that effort
to create a better

00:36:46.820 --> 00:36:49.940
understanding of how
we can get along,

00:36:49.940 --> 00:36:52.940
and how we can heal ourselves.

00:36:52.940 --> 00:36:54.390
Nobody can heal you.

00:36:54.390 --> 00:36:57.200
You have to work at
healing yourself.

00:36:57.200 --> 00:37:04.490
Because it's a personal
journey of actually addressing

00:37:04.490 --> 00:37:07.790
what happened, and coming
out on the other side feeling

00:37:07.790 --> 00:37:11.690
that you have, I have,
everybody has the right

00:37:11.690 --> 00:37:16.470
to be free of any pain that
anybody imposed upon us.

00:37:16.470 --> 00:37:21.740
That the survivors don't
agree they are wrong.

00:37:21.740 --> 00:37:26.750
They keep telling me, you
can't forgive Nazi atrocities.

00:37:26.750 --> 00:37:29.090
Did God say that?

00:37:29.090 --> 00:37:33.080
Did God decide that Nazis
are too big to forgive them?

00:37:33.080 --> 00:37:35.540
That is man's interpretation.

00:37:35.540 --> 00:37:38.736
Why can't you forgive the
big crime that really hurt,

00:37:38.736 --> 00:37:41.910
when you can forgive
the small crimes.

00:37:41.910 --> 00:37:45.020
I think we should
forgive all crimes,

00:37:45.020 --> 00:37:47.750
not for the sake
of the perpetrator,

00:37:47.750 --> 00:37:50.370
but for the sake of
healing ourselves.

00:37:50.370 --> 00:37:54.200
And once we are
healed, we hope that we

00:37:54.200 --> 00:37:59.055
can teach the perpetrators
to heal themselves too.

00:37:59.055 --> 00:38:01.430
TED GREEN: Could I jump in
here with one little shameless

00:38:01.430 --> 00:38:02.750
promotion, or another
shameless promotion?

00:38:02.750 --> 00:38:03.666
SPEAKER 1: Yeah, sure.

